#. <section class="sutta" id="sn17.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn17.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Baḷisasutta"
msgstr "2. A Hook"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn17.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa "
"yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re "
"an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn17.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bāḷisiko āmisagataṃ baḷisaṃ gambhīre udakarahade "
"pakkhipeyya."
msgstr "Suppose a fisherman was to cast a baited hook into a deep lake."

msgctxt "sn17.2:1.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro āmisacakkhu maccho gileyya."
msgstr "Seeing the bait, a fish would swallow it."

msgctxt "sn17.2:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, maccho gilabaḷiso bāḷisikassa anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ "
"āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāḷisikassa."
msgstr ""
"And so the fish that swallowed the hook would meet with tragedy and "
"disaster, and the fisherman can do what he wants with it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.2:2.1"
msgid "Bāḷisikoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Fisherman’ is a term for Māra the Wicked."

# BB translates “baited hook” but amisagata doesn’t appear here.
msgctxt "sn17.2:2.2"
msgid "Baḷisanti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Hook’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity."

# BB omits Māra here.
msgctxt "sn17.2:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ assādeti "
"nikāmeti, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gilabaḷiso mārassa anayaṃ āpanno "
"byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato."
msgstr ""
"Whoever enjoys and likes arisen possessions, honor, and popularity is called "
"a mendicant who has swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve met with tragedy and "
"disaster, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them."

msgctxt "sn17.2:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko "
"anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an "
"obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn17.2:2.5"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn17.2:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno "
"lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let "
"them occupy our minds.’"

msgctxt "sn17.2:2.7"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.2:2.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
